an hour ago

They always try to overcharge and think we don't notice. My bank statement shows that they have even charged my card twice for purchases. They always try to charge us tax on an EBT food card (which is illegal) There is a cashier in there at its always extremely rude to my children and I. We have tried smiling at her and being nice to her just to have her still be rude. We watch as she in nice to the customers in front of us and behind us. I keep all my receipts and have started having my kids always ask for receipts when ever this woman checks us out because she always over charges. The 87 cents deal for drink she would always charge my children $1 and today was my final straw. When we arrived she was out side sweeping so we were relieved that my children didn't have to be treated awful. She stopped what she was doing when they went in and ran back and YELLED at my children saying the drink prices had changed and they needed to pay attention. They went from 87 cents up to $2.06 paid with an EBT card My children said nothing, my children have never said anything when she is rude to them. We have never complained about her ALWAY over charging, we have always been nice, but this treatment is outrageous!! And I feel it is time to speak up And demand something be done! It is NOT okay for an employee to treat people that way. Especially when the customers have always been nice to her. It is the only store around that carries the squirt flavor soda that we like. And she has targeted me and my children to be cruel to!!! Something NEEDS to be done!!< /Text>

<user_name>Priscilla Usmani<//user_name>< time>
1532415687799< /time>
<rate>4< /rate>< text>
4 words: Salted Cheese Green Tea.

I was super skeptical about the name of the drink when I first heard it. I actually didn't even end up getting the drink myself because I thought it was literally melted cheese, so I got the honey lemon green tea instead.

Since my friends got the salted cheese green tea, I realized that it was basically green tea milk foam! But a way yummier, revamped version of milk foam. They also give a good foam/tea proportion.

Both drinks were delicious, you can control the sweetness which is nice. I accidentally got regular sweetness for my lemon green tea and it was a little too sweet, but eventually the ice cubes melted down and it was great.

The servings are quite big, I wish I could've ordered a smaller drink for my lemon tea.

Ps- I heard this location is better than the other one in Sunmery<//text>

< Review>
Came on the opening day. The line was out the door but the line was moving at an okay pace, so we stayed. We got the Boba Milk Tea and thought it tasted okay. The tea was really good, the tea flavor was very strong and it wasn't overly milky. The boba was standard, very chewy.

I understand it was on opening day, so it'd be fairly busy. The only problem was that they didn't tell us that they ran out of boba so we ended up waiting 40 minutes for 2 boba milk teas.   And even when we were waiting for our drinks, they did not notify their customers that there would be a bit of a wait for those who ordered boba. I was just so confused because a bunch of people were getting their drinks and we were still waiting for ours. We ended up going to the counter and asked what was up with our drinks and they just said they ran out of boba and was working on it. Overall, this place was just ok, not amazing but not bad. I just felt like the way they handled the situation just made it a very unpleasant experience.</Review>

<Pictures>None</Pictures><gmap_id>0x80e9ad43eaf4220b:0x20a36f1de1102b29< /gmap_id><Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
After a hard fall, my knees and shoulder had a lot of pain.
After going to another ortho doc in Ventura who didn't explain anything about my condition, but wanted to give me a shot in the knee, cortisone I assume.
Why would you give me anything without a diagnosis? Or even an examination?
So I asked my primary Dr to recommend someone.
An appointment with Dr Suzuki was scheduled. He had the X-ray tech do additional views. He then examined me , then went over the X-rays with me and explained my diagnosis.
My range of motion in my shoulder was severely limited . I'm needle phobic. But agreed to have a cortisone shot to my shoulder. I was VERY surprised!!! All I felt was pressure when the medicine was being injected. With in 12 hrs my range of motion improved 100%. But still a bit sore from the bruising
As for my knees, and additional shoulder treatment, he prescribed physical therapy.
I chose the Oxnard location. I couldn't be more pleased!!!  Friendly, yet highly professional. Progress is being made and hopefully I won't have to have surgery.</Text>

< review>
Small restaurant but very colorful with vibrant art on the walls.  Hand carved tables and chairs.

Service is very good and everything is made to order, so be prepared to wait.   Authentic and flavorful
Dishes ordered : Chile Relleno, Enchilada and a chicken quesadilla.  Well under $20.
All tables had patrons and other reviews state how good the place is.  Try it!< /review>

<userid>118205365009006150602<//userid>< name>
Sendy Barrows</name>
<Time>1558315524036</Time>< Rate>
3< /Rate>
< text>
The food here is great, but the service is painfully slooow!!! Make sure you are not hungry or in a hurry if you are planing on stopping by. I have eaten here before and was aware of the long wait times but this time around it definitely seem to drag on more than usual. Six of my coworkers and I stopped by for an early lunch last Thursday, there was only one other person when we walked in and it took them atleast 30 minutes to bring the food out. They also do not serve agua fresca de sangria which is kind of disappointing. The server told me they had green pozole and I figured I would give it a try, but I was not expecting to be served green pozole with a chicken leg, also the menu never mentioned  or had a picture of chicken pozole. So make sure you ask the server about the dish you are ordering if you have not eaten here before. I have posted some pictures of the menu. I have tried and would recomend the pipian rojo, flautas ahogadas, tacos dorados and both quesadillas (make sure you ask them not to fry them)  if you are not sure what to order.</text>

104177078480885682897<//user_id>
< name>
Alfred Velasquez Sr<//name>
< Time>
1555037130705< /Time>
< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< review>
IN THE MID 1950'S THIS RESTAURANT WAS KNOWN AS ROLLY'S  RESTAURANT AND IT WAS LOCATED AT THE CORNER OF OXNARD BLVD AND FORTH STREET. IT PRIMARILY SERVED AMERICAN DISHES, OVER TIME THIS RESTAURANT HAS BEEN CONVERTED INTO A MEXICAN RESTAURANT. THE INSIDE OF THE RESTAURANT IS ALWAYS VERY CLEAN INSIDE AND OUT SIDE. THE OWNER RENE WAS A COOK AT THE WELL KNOWN CIELITO LINDO RESTAURANT FOR YEARS  LOCATED ON OXNARD BLVD. COUNTRY, SUPER STAR SINGER WILLIE NELSON AND OTHER CELEBRITIES ENJOY RENE'S CHILI RELLENOS AND GROUND BEEF ENCHILADAS. DURING THEIR  VISIT TO OXNARD  WHILE THEY RECORDED  WILLIE NELSON CD AT THE OLD MOVIE THEATER ON OXNARD BLVD BETWEEN  6th AND 7th STREET, AFTER DECADES OF  OWNING BAHIA RESTAURANT, RENE STILL SERVES THE INCREDIBLY CHILI RELLENOS AND BEEF ENCHILADAS AND OTHER GREAT DISHES. ONCE YOU TRY RENE'S CHILI RELLENOS AND ENCHILADAS I AM SURE YOU WILL BE BACK.
P.S, IN 1954 I WAS 10 YEARS OLD AND I WOULD WALK INTO ROLLY'S RESTAURANT DAILY TO SELL THE OXNARD PRESS COURIER NEWS PAPER TO CUSTOMERS FOR A NICKEL. THOSE WERE THE GOOD OLD DAYS GROWING UP IN OXNARD " THE PRESS COURIER'S PRINTING DEPARTMENT
WAS ACROSS THE ALLEY NEXT TO THE POST OFFICE ON 4th AND C ST.
AL VELASQUEZ SR< /review>

< Review>
Came here for dinner one evening.  Not crowded.  Ordered the Caldo de siete mares which was wonderful!  The soup came with seven different seafoods: clam, muscle, scallops, shrimp, octopus, fish, and crab which was reasonably priced.  Would definitely come back again.  Waitress spoke little english but we made out just fine.</Review>

< review>
My wife and I stayed in Mariposa for part of our 2nd honeymoon to visit Yosemite, with the second leg in the eastern sierra's. We figured (judging by restaurant prices) that everything in town would be tourist prices, including the market. Our stay in Mariposa didn't have a kitchenette, but our next destination did. I knew from experience our desitination in the eastern sierras would have exhorbitant tourist prices for groceries, so we planned on buying perishables at Pioneer Market before leaving Mariposa. We bought all non-perishables at a Walmart en route to Mariposa. We were pleasantly surprised to find a full-service supermarket with prices competitive to back home, some items even cheaper than buying at Walmart, Food4Less, or Costco back home.<//review>
